Name: pin-init
License File: LICENSE-APACHE
Description: Library to safely and fallibly initialize pinned structs using in-place constructors.

* What is this crate used for?
Initializing pinned structs -- especially useful where C++ and Rust need to share layouts.

* Are there any use restrictions? i.e. only for development hosts
No.

* What differs from upstream? Include a changelog if feasible.
The released crate on crates.io does not include license files for the
pin-init-internal crate.  This fork uses the upstream git commit which
includes licenses files.  Once releases of the crates are made with those
files included, we can remove the fork.

* Are there any restrictions to how it should be rolled?
pin-init will be used in sensitive repositories -- downstream dependency
teams should be informed so that they can ensure any additional testing is
completed.

* Is there anything else which makes this dependency "special"?
No.
